{
  "$comment": "BridgeCircle feature-parity manifest. Every user-facing feature is declared here with the platforms and window-size layouts it must be tested on. parity/check-parity.mjs enforces it: web coverage = a Playwright spec tagged @feature:<id> (app/tests/e2e), mobile coverage = a Maestro flow tagged feature:<id> (mobile/e2e/flows). Layout coverage: web 'expanded' is satisfied by any tagged spec (desktop project); 'compact'/'medium' need a spec also tagged @layout:compact / @layout:medium; mobile 'compact' is satisfied by any tagged flow (phone runner); mobile 'expanded' needs a flow tagged layout:expanded (tablet runner). Every page.tsx route must be claimed by exactly one feature — adding a page without a manifest entry fails CI, and a manifest entry without tests on every declared platform fails CI unless the gap is consciously recorded in parity-baseline.txt. Run: node parity/check-parity.mjs [--update]",
